.TH "hwmon_device_register_with_info" 9 "hwmon_device_register_with_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hwmon_device_register_with_info \- register w/ hwmon
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct device *" hwmon_device_register_with_info
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "const char *name "  ","
.BI "void *drvdata "  ","
.BI "const struct hwmon_chip_info *chip "  ","
.BI "const struct attribute_group **extra_groups "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
the parent device
.IP "name" 12
hwmon name attribute
.IP "drvdata" 12
driver data to attach to created device
.IP "chip" 12
pointer to hwmon chip information
.IP "extra_groups" 12
pointer to list of additional non-standard attribute groups
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBhwmon_device_unregister\fP must be called when the device is no
longer needed.

Returns the pointer to the new device.
